  "body": "### User Story\n\nAs a user, I want to have two-pane UI on large screens (tablet—ã f.ex.) so that I don't have to spend time navigating back and forth from messages list to chat list.\n\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Feature\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n*Summary*: On the big screens, when space allows it would be more convenient to use two-pane UI. We already have a design for it - https://www.figma.com/file/YS5wVm8MDFvbmXROj1oMZmM4/Tablet-Desktop?node-id=1%3A2\n\n#### Expected behavior\nWhen space allows, Status UI become two-pane to fit more information for user\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\n\n#### Actual behavior\nCurrently even on a big tablet screens user see only one pane with info. That makes navigating more tedious.\n\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)",
